  <metadata>
    <id>Ninject.PCL111</id>
    <version>1.0-alpha1</version>
    <title>Ninject PCL 111</title>
    <authors>qbus00 - Jakub Kaprzyk porting to PCL111, Oren Novotny original author</authors>
    <owners />
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/qbus00/ninject.pcl111/raw/master/LICENSE.txt</licenseUrl>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/qbus00/ninject.pcl111</projectUrl>

    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>
		This is a modification of Portable.Ninject (https://github.com/onovotny/ninject/) which is compiled in PCL 111 profile. 
		It means that this library can be used both in PCL and .NET Standard libraries (which is not possible when using original Portable.Ninject). 
		Another addition is LinkerPleaseInclude class which preserves the most important parts of Ninject which are normally removed in full linker mode because of reflection.
    </description>
    <summary>IoC container for .NET</summary>
    <releaseNotes>Initial release with support for PCL profile 111, Android and iOS</releaseNotes>
    <tags>Ninject ioc di portable pcl xamarin ios android monotouch monoandroid</tags>
  </metadata>
